Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Soak your @bamboo skewers{4} in cold water to prevent them from burning.

Cut the @British chicken thighs{3} into 2cm chunks, then add them to a #medium bowl{} and stir in half the @harissa paste{100%g}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Thread the chicken pieces onto the skewers (2 per person). Transfer the skewers to one side of a lightly oiled large #baking tray{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and cut the @lemon{1} into wedges.

Spread the @McCain home chips{400%g} on another large baking tray in a single layer. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

When the oven is hot, bake the chips on the middle shelf, ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl{}, combine the garlic, @panko breadcrumbs{10%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and half the remaining harissa, then add the @lamb mince{200%g}. Season with @pepper{} and mix together with your hands.

Shape into mini sausage shapes, 4 per person. Flatten to make koftas. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the koftas onto the other side of the chicken baking tray.

When the chips have been baking for ~{15%minutes}, bake the skewers and koftas on the top shelf until cooked through, ~{12-16%minutes}. Turn halfway through. IMPORTANT: The chicken and koftas are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While everything bakes, clean the medium bowl. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}.

In the (now clean) bowl, mix together a good squeeze of lemon juice, the @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir the tomatoes into the dressing.

In a separate #small bowl{}, mix together the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}, lemon zest and remaining harissa. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Set both aside for now. Use any free time to do some washing up.

Just before everything's ready, pop the @Greek style flatbreads{2} into the oven until warm and starting to turn golden, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Place the @ready to eat falafels{171%g} on a #plate{} and microwave, 800W: ~{75%seconds} / 900W: ~{45%seconds} / 1000W: ~{30%seconds}. If you don't have a #microwave{}, place the falafels onto a #baking tray{} and bake in the oven until golden brown, ~{5-8%minutes}.

Spread half the harissa yoghurt onto the warmed flatbreads.

When everything's ready, spoon the @houmous{100%g} onto the bottom of a #serving plate{} and top with the falafels. Drizzle over half the @red pepper chilli jelly{50%g}.

Transfer the harissa flatbreads to a serving plate and top with the lamb koftas and a small handful of the @baby leaf mix{50%g}. Drizzle over the remaining harissa yoghurt. Lay the chicken shawarma onto another serving plate and drizzle over the remaining red pepper chilli jelly.

Mix the remaining baby leaves with the lemon dressing and tomatoes. Transfer the salad to a #serving bowl{}, then serve alongside the chips and the remaining lemon wedges for squeezing over.

Share and tuck in. Enjoy!